  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for xorg-x11-server",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for xorg-x11-server fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2021-4009: The handler for the CreatePointerBarrier request of the XFixes \n  extension does not properly validate the request length leading to out of \n  bounds memory write. (bsc#1190487)\n- CVE-2021-4011: The handlers for the RecordCreateContext and RecordRegisterClients\n  requests of the Record extension do not properly validate the request\n  length leading to out of bounds memory write. (bsc#1190489)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
